    <title type="html"><![CDATA[Install Redmine 2.1.0 on Ubuntu Server 12.04 64bit]]></title>
    <link href="http://www.developerof.com/blog/2012/09/23/install-redmine-2-dot-1-0-on-ubuntu-server-12-dot-04-64-bit/"/>
    <updated>2012-09-23T16:30:00+02:00</updated>
    <id>http://www.developerof.com/blog/2012/09/23/install-redmine-2-dot-1-0-on-ubuntu-server-12-dot-04-64-bit</id>
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<p>We have been using Redmine for issue tracking and wiki since 2010. Thanks to wiki, everyone is able to access and share information. Major topics are:</p>

<ul>
<li>How to create a new developer environment?</li>
<li>Rules and conventions: continuous delivery, version number syntax, CI job configuration, coding style, creating specification, etc.</li>
<li>SCM description: how to perform a build and deployment.</li>
<li>Runtime environments' data (test, CI, production, DVCS).</li>
</ul>


<p>We don't share constant information over email. If this information isn't in our wiki, then</p>

<blockquote><p>We write it into the wiki, and share wiki page.</p></blockquote>

<p><strong>Wiki helps you to eliminate waste!</strong> Let's see the installation process!</p>

<!--more-->


<p><div class='bogus-wrapper'><notextile><figure class='code'><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class=''><span class='line'>sudo su -</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure></notextile></div></p>

<h3>Install LAMP server</h3>

<p><div class='bogus-wrapper'><notextile><figure class='code'><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class=''><span class='line'>tasksel install lamp-server</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure></notextile></div>
Set mysql root password, you need it later! [<em>ref. MYSQL_ROOT_PASSWORD</em>]</p>

<h3>Install infrastructure</h3>

<p><div class='bogus-wrapper'><notextile><figure class='code'><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class=''><span class='line'>apt-get install ruby-full libmysqlclient-dev libmagickwand-dev libapache2-mod-passenger</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure></notextile></div></p>

<p>Note: After this operation, 306 MB of additional disk space will be used.</p>

<h3>Install Redmine 2.1.0</h3>

<p><div class='bogus-wrapper'><notextile><figure class='code'><figcaption><span>Create Redmine database </span></figcaption>
<div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
<span class='line-number'>2</span>
<span class='line-number'>3</span>
<span class='line-number'>4</span>
<span class='line-number'>5</span>
<span class='line-number'>6</span>
<span class='line-number'>7</span>
<span class='line-number'>8</span>
<span class='line-number'>9</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class=''><span class='line'>&lt;/p>
</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'>&lt;h1>You need MYSQL_ROOT_PASSWORD!&lt;/h1>
</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'>&lt;p>mysql -u root -p
</span><span class='line'>create database redmine character set utf8;
</span><span class='line'>create user 'redmine'@'localhost' identified by 'REDMINEDB_PASSWORD';
</span><span class='line'>grant all privileges on redmine.* to 'redmine'@'localhost';
</span><span class='line'>exit</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure></notextile></div>
You need <em>REDMINEDB_PASSWORD</em> later!</p>

<p><div class='bogus-wrapper'><notextile><figure class='code'><figcaption><span>Download Redmine </span></figcaption>
<div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
<span class='line-number'>2</span>
<span class='line-number'>3</span>
<span class='line-number'>4</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class=''><span class='line'>wget http://rubyforge.org/frs/download.php/76448/redmine-2.1.0.tar.gz
</span><span class='line'>tar xzvf redmine-2.1.0.tar.gz
</span><span class='line'>mv redmine-2.1.0 redmine
</span><span class='line'>mv redmine /var/www/redmine</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure></notextile></div></p>

<h3>Configure Redmine 2.1.0</h3>

<p><div class='bogus-wrapper'><notextile><figure class='code'><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
<span class='line-number'>2</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class=''><span class='line'>cd /var/www/redmine
</span><span class='line'>cp config/database.yml.example config/database.yml</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure></notextile></div></p>

<p><div class='bogus-wrapper'><notextile><figure class='code'><figcaption><span>Settings Redmine Edit database.yml </span></figcaption>
 <div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
<span class='line-number'>2</span>
<span class='line-number'>3</span>
<span class='line-number'>4</span>
<span class='line-number'>5</span>
<span class='line-number'>6</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class='yaml'><span class='line'><span class="l-Scalar-Plain">production</span><span class="p-Indicator">:</span>
</span><span class='line'><span class="l-Scalar-Plain">adapter</span><span class="p-Indicator">:</span>        <span class="l-Scalar-Plain">mysql</span>
</span><span class='line'><span class="l-Scalar-Plain">database</span><span class="p-Indicator">:</span>       <span class="l-Scalar-Plain">redmine</span>
</span><span class='line'><span class="l-Scalar-Plain">host</span><span class="p-Indicator">:</span>           <span class="l-Scalar-Plain">localhost</span>
</span><span class='line'><span class="l-Scalar-Plain">username</span><span class="p-Indicator">:</span>       <span class="l-Scalar-Plain">redmine</span>
</span><span class='line'><span class="l-Scalar-Plain">password</span><span class="p-Indicator">:</span>       <span class="l-Scalar-Plain">REDMINEDB_PASSWORD</span>
</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure></notextile></div></p>

<p><div class='bogus-wrapper'><notextile><figure class='code'><figcaption><span>Install Rake </span></figcaption>
<div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
<span class='line-number'>2</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class=''><span class='line'>apt-get install rake
</span><span class='line'>apt-get install ruby-bundler</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure></notextile></div></p>

<p>The next step will take a while (about 2 minutes):</p>

<p><div class='bogus-wrapper'><notextile><figure class='code'><figcaption><span>Install Rake </span></figcaption>
<div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
<span class='line-number'>2</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class=''><span class='line'>cd config
</span><span class='line'>bundle install --without development test postgresql sqlite</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure></notextile></div>
You must get <em>"Your bundle is complete! Use <code>bundle show [gemname]</code> to see where a bundled gem is installed."</em>
<div class='bogus-wrapper'><notextile><figure class='code'><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class=''><span class='line'>rake generate_secret_token</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure></notextile></div></p>

<p><div class='bogus-wrapper'><notextile><figure class='code'><figcaption><span>Initialize Redmine  </span></figcaption>
 <div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
<span class='line-number'>2</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class='ruby'><span class='line'><span class="no">RAILS_ENV</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="n">production</span> <span class="n">rake</span> <span class="n">db</span><span class="ss">:migrate</span>
</span><span class='line'><span class="no">RAILS_ENV</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="n">production</span> <span class="n">rake</span> <span class="n">redmine</span><span class="ss">:load_default_data</span>
</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure></notextile></div></p>

<h3>Settings Apache</h3>

<p><div class='bogus-wrapper'><notextile><figure class='code'><figcaption><span>Edit /etc/apache2/mods-available/passenger.conf  </span></figcaption>
 <div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class='apache'><span class='line'><span class="nb">PassengerDefaultUser</span> www-database
</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure></notextile></div></p>

<p><div class='bogus-wrapper'><notextile><figure class='code'><figcaption><span>Edit /etc/apache2/sites-available/default  </span></figcaption>
 <div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
<span class='line-number'>2</span>
<span class='line-number'>3</span>
<span class='line-number'>4</span>
<span class='line-number'>5</span>
<span class='line-number'>6</span>
<span class='line-number'>7</span>
<span class='line-number'>8</span>
<span class='line-number'>9</span>
<span class='line-number'>10</span>
<span class='line-number'>11</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class='apache'><span class='line'><span class="nt">&lt;/p&gt;</span>
</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'><span class="nt">&lt;h1&gt;</span><span class="nb">Overwrite</span> Document root&lt;/h1&gt;
</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'><span class="nt">&lt;p&gt;</span><span class="nb">DocumentRoot</span> <span class="sx">/var/www/redmine/public</span>&lt;/p&gt;
</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'><span class="nt">&lt;h1&gt;</span><span class="nb">Add</span> Directory element&lt;/h1&gt;
</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'><span class="nt">&lt;p&gt;&lt;Directory</span> <span class="s">/var/www/redmine</span><span class="nt">&gt;</span>
</span><span class='line'>  <span class="nb">RailsBaseURI</span> <span class="sx">/redmine</span>
</span><span class='line'><span class="nt">&lt;/Directory&gt;</span>
</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure></notextile></div></p>

<p><div class='bogus-wrapper'><notextile><figure class='code'><figcaption><span>Set permissions and restart apache2 </span></figcaption>
<div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
<span class='line-number'>2</span>
<span class='line-number'>3</span>
<span class='line-number'>4</span>
<span class='line-number'>5</span>
<span class='line-number'>6</span>
<span class='line-number'>7</span>
<span class='line-number'>8</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class=''><span class='line'>a2enmod passenger
</span><span class='line'>cd /var/www
</span><span class='line'>mkdir redmine/public/plugin_assets
</span><span class='line'>chown -R www-data:www-data redmine/
</span><span class='line'>chmod -R 755 redmine/
</span><span class='line'>chmod -R 777 redmine/public/plugin_assets
</span><span class='line'>chmod -R 777 redmine/files
</span><span class='line'>service apache2 restart</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure></notextile></div></p>

<p>After all you get an ugly message: <em>apache2: "Could not reliably determine the server's fully qualified domain name, using 127.0.1.1 for ServerName"</em></p>

<p><div class='bogus-wrapper'><notextile><figure class='code'><figcaption><span>Set server's FQ name, edit /etc/apache2/httpd.conf  </span></figcaption>
 <div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
<span class='line-number'>2</span>
<span class='line-number'>3</span>
<span class='line-number'>4</span>
<span class='line-number'>5</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class='apache'><span class='line'><span class="nt">&lt;/p&gt;</span>
</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'><span class="nt">&lt;h1&gt;</span><span class="nb">Change</span> &#39;localhost&#39; to real server name&lt;/h1&gt;
</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'><span class="nt">&lt;p&gt;</span><span class="nb">ServerName</span> YOUR_REAL_SERVER_NAME
</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure></notextile></div></p>

<p><div class='bogus-wrapper'><notextile><figure class='code'><figcaption><span>Restart apache </span></figcaption>
<div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class=''><span class='line'>service apache2 restart</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure></notextile></div></p>

<p>Navigate browser to redmine server address, and redmine login page will be shown.</p>

<blockquote><p>Change default admin/admin user's password!!!</p></blockquote>

<p><strong>Do not forget</strong> Redmine host name settings after login: Click <em>Setting,</em> choose <em>General Tab</em> and set <em>Host name and path</em> to YOUR_REAL_SERVER_NAME</p>

<h2>Conclusion</h2>

<p><img class="left" src="/images/post/redmine1.png" title="Redmine" >
All company must have a central knowledge base that easily access by team members. Use Redmine wiki to share <strong>same information</strong> to everyone and everywhere! <strong>Wiki helps you to eliminate waste!</strong></p>
]]></content>
